\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Branch prediction decision chain, spanning the ID stage (blue) and EX-stage feedback (orange). Bimodal confidence gating bypasses the perceptron for easy branches. The early-stop rule $|s_i|>(n-i)\,W_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}$ terminates dot-product computation once the result sign is determined. Mispredictions trigger both pipeline flushing and online weight updates.\relax }}{6}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:bp-chain}{{2}{6}{Branch prediction decision chain, spanning the ID stage (blue) and EX-stage feedback (orange). Bimodal confidence gating bypasses the perceptron for easy branches. The early-stop rule $|s_i|>(n-i)\,W_{\max }$ terminates dot-product computation once the result sign is determined. Mispredictions trigger both pipeline flushing and online weight updates.\relax }{figure.caption.3}{}}
